# Code Review Rules

## Blocking Issues (Must Fix)

- Missing auth middleware on mutating routes
- Secrets or credentials in code
- Unvalidated user input
- Unescaped user content in HTML/JS output
- Failing tests
- Missing tests for new routes

## Review Checklist

- [ ] `catchAsync` on async handlers
- [ ] Joi validation for form data
- [ ] Authorization middleware for protected actions
- [ ] Flash messages on success/error
- [ ] No unused imports or commented-out code
- [ ] Docs updated if behavior changed
- [ ] `npm test` passes

## Feedback Levels

- **Nit:** Optional style (prefix "Nit:")
- **Suggestion:** Worth considering
- **Blocking:** Must fix (security, bugs, missing tests)

## Conventions

- CommonJS, not ES modules
- POST-Redirect-GET pattern
- Imperative commit messages

Reference: `docs/standards/CODE_REVIEW_GUIDE.md`
